Dear Granma

It’s a lily cheesy, you may be thinking “what in carnation!?”, but thistle be good. I beleaf it’s time to put the petal to the metal once and floral. Just pollen your leg, no bud omen here, it’s not really once and floral, actually it’s the opposiete. It’s just thyme I rose to the occasion after the many “oopsie daisy” days, so if it’s bouquet with you I have you clovered on the floral front for the next 12 months.

Love, David
